  "prompt": "When someone married says he loves me, yet he has no intention of leaving his wife and daughter, should I believe him and love him back?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're experiencing this difficult situation. Navigating relationships where one person is committed to someone else can be incredibly challenging and emotionally taxing. Here are a few things to consider:\n\n1. **Assess Your Feelings and Needs:** Reflect on what you truly want in a relationship. Consider whether being involved with someone who is not fully available emotionally or practically aligns with your long-term happiness and well-being.\n\n2. **Understand His Intentions:** If he has explicitly stated that he does not intend to leave his wife and daughter, it's important to take his words seriously. Continuing a relationship under these circumstances can lead to ongoing emotional strain and uncertainty.\n\n3. **Consider the Impact:** Think about the potential consequences for all parties involved, including yourself, his family, and any children. Relationships built on unclear intentions can sometimes lead to complications and hurt feelings down the line.\n\n4. **Seek Support:** Talking to trusted friends, family members, or a professional counselor can provide you with additional perspectives and support as you navigate your feelings and decisions.\n\n5. **Prioritize Your Well-being:** Your emotional health is paramount. It's important to make choices that honor your feelings and contribute positively to your life.\n\nUltimately, the decision is deeply personal, and it's important to prioritize what feels right for you while considering the broader implications of the situation.",
